			<ns0:name>pa...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101628056640429344673/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The x86-32 validator does not accept the instruction, but the x86-64 validator does.  Let's be consistent and disallow 0x666690 on x86-64.  The binutils use another 3-byte alternative as a nop: 0x0f1f00.  I grepped through all libraries in 64bit glibc toolchain and the sequence 0x666690 was never found there.  So it should be safe to disallow it.

Additionally the discussed instruction is not in the list of recommended NOP sequences as per intel manual, theoretically it's semantics may change in future processors.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-07-22T22:11:07.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-07-19T15:03:47.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
